commit.message: Update dependencies
Update gem metadata
Update license specifiers
Add the current maintainer to the list of authors

Update the list of packaged files

Do not pack examples, specs, manual, and files that are only useful
in development.

Update gem signing

This way it generates fewer warnings.

Remove load path from gemspec

It's the same as the default so no point specifying it.
Move description up top.
Update certificate

Really fix encryption issue

The previous fix incorrectly escaped "\r" as "\\\r". However, it needs
to be escaped as "\\r" (so backslash followed by letter r).

The previous fix incorrectly escaped "\r" as "\\\r". However, it needs
to be escaped as "\\r" (so backslash followed by letter r).

commit.message:
Fix missing glyph width.

Prawn correctly used width of missing glyphs to layout text but didn't
encode the widths correctly in subset fonts. The resulted in characters
with missing glyphs to have 0 width. And even though Prawn drawn
Replacement Character glyphs they were stacking on top of each other
because their widths were wrong.

Fix missing glyph width.

Prawn correctly used width of missing glyphs to layout text but didn't
encode the widths correctly in subset fonts. The resulted in characters
with missing glyphs to have 0 width. And even though Prawn drawn
Replacement Character glyphs they were stacking on top of each other
because their widths were wrong.
